[2026-03-12T15:44:25Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R2M2QWo1exTvtiuqbTLU8f","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# Installation\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3ÔćĺThis document covers the various ways to install Cloche on your machine.\n     4Ôćĺ\n     5Ôćĺ## Prerequisites\n     6Ôćĺ\n     7ÔćĺAll installation methods require:\n     8Ôćĺ\n     9Ôćĺ- **Docker** ÔÇö Cloche runs workflows in containers\n    10Ôćĺ- **Git** ÔÇö result extraction uses git worktrees\n    11Ôćĺ- **`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`** ÔÇö for agent steps using Claude Code\n    12Ôćĺ\n    13Ôćĺ## Build from Source\n    14Ôćĺ\n    15ÔćĺClone the repository, build the binaries and Docker image, and install them:\n    16Ôćĺ\n    17Ôćĺ```\n    18Ôćĺgit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    19Ôćĺcd cloche\n    20Ôćĺmake install\n    21Ôćĺ```\n    22Ôćĺ\n    23Ôćĺ`make install` builds all three binaries (`cloche`, `cloched`, `cloche-agent`),\n    24Ôćĺbuilds the `cloche-agent:latest` Docker image, installs the binaries to\n    25Ôćĺ`~/.local/bin/`, and starts the daemon. You can change the install prefix:\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27Ôćĺ```\n    28Ôćĺmake install PREFIX=/usr/local\n    29Ôćĺ```\n    30Ôćĺ\n    31ÔćĺMake sure the install prefix is on your `PATH`:\n    32Ôćĺ\n    33Ôćĺ```\n    34Ôćĺexport PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n    35Ôćĺ```\n    36Ôćĺ\n    37Ôćĺ### Build Requirements\n    38Ôćĺ\n    39Ôćĺ- Go 1.25+\n    40Ôćĺ\n    41Ôćĺ## `go install`\n    42Ôćĺ\n    43ÔćĺIf you have Go installed, you can install the binaries directly:\n    44Ôćĺ\n    45Ôćĺ```\n    46Ôćĺgo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche@latest\n    47Ôćĺgo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloched@latest\n    48Ôćĺgo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche-agent@latest\n    49Ôćĺ```\n    50Ôćĺ\n    51ÔćĺThis places the binaries in `$GOPATH/bin` (or `$HOME/go/bin` by default).\n    52Ôćĺ\n    53ÔćĺYou still need to build the Docker image separately. Clone the repository and\n    54Ôćĺrun:\n    55Ôćĺ\n    56Ôćĺ```\n    57Ôćĺgit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    58Ôćĺcd cloche\n    59Ôćĺmake docker-build\n    60Ôćĺ```\n    61Ôćĺ\n    62Ôćĺ## Pre-built Release Binaries (Planned)\n    63Ôćĺ\n    64Ôćĺ> **Note:** Pre-built release binaries are not yet available. This section\n    65Ôćĺ> describes the planned installation method for when releases are published.\n    66Ôćĺ\n    67ÔćĺDownload pre-built binaries from the\n    68Ôćĺ[GitHub Releases](https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases) page. Each\n    69Ôćĺrelease will include archives for common platforms (Linux amd64, Linux arm64,\n    70ÔćĺmacOS amd64, macOS arm64).\n    71Ôćĺ\n    72Ôćĺ```\n    73Ôćĺ# Example: Linux amd64\n    74Ôćĺcurl -LO https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases/latest/download/cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\n    75Ôćĺtar xzf cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\n    76Ôćĺsudo install cloche cloched cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/\n    77Ôćĺ```\n    78Ôćĺ\n    79ÔćĺYou still need to build the Docker image. Clone the repo and run\n    80Ôćĺ`make docker-build`:\n    81Ôćĺ\n    82Ôćĺ```\n    83Ôćĺgit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    84Ôćĺcd cloche\n    85Ôćĺmake docker-build\n    86Ôćĺ```\n    87Ôćĺ\n    88Ôćĺ## Homebrew (macOS / Linux) (Planned)\n    89Ôćĺ\n    90Ôćĺ> **Note:** A Homebrew tap is not yet published. This section describes the\n    91Ôćĺ> planned installation method.\n    92Ôćĺ\n    93Ôćĺ```\n    94Ôćĺbrew tap cloche-dev/tap\n    95Ôćĺbrew install cloche\n    96Ôćĺ```\n    97Ôćĺ\n    98ÔćĺThis will install all three binaries. You will still need the Docker image ÔÇö\n    99Ôćĺthe formula will print post-install instructions for building or pulling it.\n   100Ôćĺ\n   101Ôćĺ## Docker-Only Usage (Planned)\n   102Ôćĺ\n   103Ôćĺ> **Note:** A dedicated `Dockerfile.daemon` for running the daemon in Docker\n   104Ôćĺ> does not exist yet. This section describes a planned future option.\n   105Ôćĺ\n   106ÔćĺRunning the Cloche daemon inside Docker would avoid any host installation\n   107Ôćĺbeyond Docker itself. This would be useful for CI environments or trying Cloche\n   108Ôćĺwithout installing Go.\n   109Ôćĺ\n   110ÔćĺOnce available, usage would look like:\n   111Ôćĺ\n   112Ôćĺ```\n   113Ôćĺdocker run -d \\\n   114Ôćĺ  --name cloched \\\n   115Ôćĺ  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n   116Ôćĺ  -v /tmp/cloche.sock:/tmp/cloche.sock \\\n   117Ôćĺ  -e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY \\\n   118Ôćĺ  cloche-daemon\n   119Ôćĺ```\n   120Ôćĺ\n   121ÔćĺDocker-in-Docker requires mounting the Docker socket. The CLI (`cloche`)\n   122Ôćĺstill needs to be available on the host (or in the same container) to\n   123Ôćĺcommunicate with the daemon over the Unix socket.\n   124Ôćĺ\n   125Ôćĺ## Verifying the Installation\n   126Ôćĺ\n   127ÔćĺAfter installing, verify that everything works:\n   128Ôćĺ\n   129Ôćĺ```\n   130Ôćĺ# Check the binaries\n   131Ôćĺcloche --help\n   132Ôćĺcloched --help\n   133Ôćĺ\n   134Ôćĺ# Start the daemon (if not already running)\n   135Ôćĺcloched &\n   136Ôćĺ\n   137Ôćĺ# Build the agent image\n   138Ôćĺmake docker-build\n   139Ôćĺ\n   140Ôćĺ# Run a quick test from any git repository with a .cloche/ directory\n   141Ôćĺcloche list\n   142Ôćĺ```\n   143Ôćĺ\n   144Ôćĺ## Upgrading\n   145Ôćĺ\n   146ÔćĺTo upgrade an existing installation, repeat your original installation method.\n   147ÔćĺIf you built from source:\n   148Ôćĺ\n   149Ôćĺ```\n   150Ôćĺcd cloche\n   151Ôćĺgit pull\n   152Ôćĺmake install\n   153Ôćĺ```\n   154Ôćĺ\n   155ÔćĺThe `make install` target stops the running daemon, installs the new binaries,\n   156Ôćĺand restarts the daemon automatically.\n   157Ôćĺ\n   158Ôćĺ## Next Steps\n   159Ôćĺ\n   160Ôćĺ- [Usage guide](USAGE.md) ÔÇö quick start, CLI reference, and workflow setup\n   161Ôćĺ- [Workflow DSL reference](workflows.md) ÔÇö full syntax for `.cloche` files\n   162Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"221369ce-d654-4cd4-877a-e329688c1fa8","uuid":"decffd62-03b5-4311-b9e1-1007721eaa2a","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md","content":"# Installation\n\nThis document covers the various ways to install Cloche on your machine.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\nAll installation methods require:\n\n- **Docker** ÔÇö Cloche runs workflows in containers\n- **Git** ÔÇö result extraction uses git worktrees\n- **`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`** ÔÇö for agent steps using Claude Code\n\n## Build from Source\n\nClone the repository, build the binaries and Docker image, and install them:\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\ncd cloche\nmake install\n```\n\n`make install` builds all three binaries (`cloche`, `cloched`, `cloche-agent`),\nbuilds the `cloche-agent:latest` Docker image, installs the binaries to\n`~/.local/bin/`, and starts the daemon. You can change the install prefix:\n\n```\nmake install PREFIX=/usr/local\n```\n\nMake sure the install prefix is on your `PATH`:\n\n```\nexport PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n```\n\n### Build Requirements\n\n- Go 1.25+\n\n## `go install`\n\nIf you have Go installed, you can install the binaries directly:\n\n```\ngo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche@latest\ngo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloched@latest\ngo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche-agent@latest\n```\n\nThis places the binaries in `$GOPATH/bin` (or `$HOME/go/bin` by default).\n\nYou still need to build the Docker image separately. Clone the repository and\nrun:\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\ncd cloche\nmake docker-build\n```\n\n## Pre-built Release Binaries (Planned)\n\n> **Note:** Pre-built release binaries are not yet available. This section\n> describes the planned installation method for when releases are published.\n\nDownload pre-built binaries from the\n[GitHub Releases](https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases) page. Each\nrelease will include archives for common platforms (Linux amd64, Linux arm64,\nmacOS amd64, macOS arm64).\n\n```\n# Example: Linux amd64\ncurl -LO https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases/latest/download/cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\ntar xzf cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\nsudo install cloche cloched cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/\n```\n\nYou still need to build the Docker image. Clone the repo and run\n`make docker-build`:\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\ncd cloche\nmake docker-build\n```\n\n## Homebrew (macOS / Linux) (Planned)\n\n> **Note:** A Homebrew tap is not yet published. This section describes the\n> planned installation method.\n\n```\nbrew tap cloche-dev/tap\nbrew install cloche\n```\n\nThis will install all three binaries. You will still need the Docker image ÔÇö\nthe formula will print post-install instructions for building or pulling it.\n\n## Docker-Only Usage (Planned)\n\n> **Note:** A dedicated `Dockerfile.daemon` for running the daemon in Docker\n> does not exist yet. This section describes a planned future option.\n\nRunning the Cloche daemon inside Docker would avoid any host installation\nbeyond Docker itself. This would be useful for CI environments or trying Cloche\nwithout installing Go.\n\nOnce available, usage would look like:\n\n```\ndocker run -d \\\n  --name cloched \\\n  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n  -v /tmp/cloche.sock:/tmp/cloche.sock \\\n  -e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY \\\n  cloche-daemon\n```\n\nDocker-in-Docker requires mounting the Docker socket. The CLI (`cloche`)\nstill needs to be available on the host (or in the same container) to\ncommunicate with the daemon over the Unix socket.\n\n## Verifying the Installation\n\nAfter installing, verify that everything works:\n\n```\n# Check the binaries\ncloche --help\ncloched --help\n\n# Start the daemon (if not already running)\ncloched &\n\n# Build the agent image\nmake docker-build\n\n# Run a quick test from any git repository with a .cloche/ directory\ncloche list\n```\n\n## Upgrading\n\nTo upgrade an existing installation, repeat your original installation method.\nIf you built from source:\n\n```\ncd cloche\ngit pull\nmake install\n```\n\nThe `make install` target stops the running daemon, installs the new binaries,\nand restarts the daemon automatically.\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Usage guide](USAGE.md) ÔÇö quick start, CLI reference, and workflow setup\n- [Workflow DSL reference](workflows.md) ÔÇö full syntax for `.cloche` files\n","numLines":162,"startLine":1,"totalLines":162}}}
[2026-03-12T15:44:25Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015r3rgm9S3HxT3bnhfQPA2t","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KfPjyNiuFbNDTLWAuWQwPk","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2588,"cache_read_input_tokens":16283,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2588},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"221369ce-d654-4cd4-877a-e329688c1fa8","uuid":"b151526c-7513-4c9d-b2fc-dd8e34d79442"}
[2026-03-12T15:44:25Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KfPjyNiuFbNDTLWAuWQwPk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# Cloche Usage\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3ÔćĺCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4Ôćĺworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5Ôćĺcontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6Ôćĺresults to a git branch.\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8Ôćĺ## Core Concepts\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10Ôćĺ- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11Ôćĺ- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12Ôćĺ- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13Ôćĺ- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14Ôćĺ- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15Ôćĺ\n    16Ôćĺ## Workflow DSL\n    17Ôćĺ\n    18ÔćĺWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19Ôćĺdeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20Ôćĺno orphans, entry point exists).\n    21Ôćĺ\n    22Ôćĺ### Minimal Example\n    23Ôćĺ\n    24Ôćĺ```\n    25Ôćĺworkflow \"develop\" {\n    26Ôćĺ  step implement {\n    27Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    29Ôćĺ  }\n    30Ôćĺ\n    31Ôćĺ  step test {\n    32Ôćĺ    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    34Ôćĺ  }\n    35Ôćĺ\n    36Ôćĺ  implement:success -> test\n    37Ôćĺ  implement:fail -> abort\n    38Ôćĺ  test:success -> done\n    39Ôćĺ  test:fail -> abort\n    40Ôćĺ}\n    41Ôćĺ```\n    42Ôćĺ\n    43Ôćĺ### Step Configuration\n    44Ôćĺ\n    45Ôćĺ| Key | Type | Description |\n    46Ôćĺ|-----|------|-------------|\n    47Ôćĺ| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48Ôćĺ| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49Ôćĺ| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50Ôćĺ| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51Ôćĺ| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52Ôćĺ| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53Ôćĺ| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54Ôćĺ| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55Ôćĺ| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56Ôćĺ| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57Ôćĺ\n    58ÔćĺA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59Ôćĺ\n    60Ôćĺ### The `file()` Function\n    61Ôćĺ\n    62Ôćĺ`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63Ôćĺ(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64Ôćĺtemplates:\n    65Ôćĺ\n    66Ôćĺ```\n    67Ôćĺprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68Ôćĺ```\n    69Ôćĺ\n    70Ôćĺ### The `container {}` Block\n    71Ôćĺ\n    72ÔćĺCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73Ôćĺ\n    74Ôćĺ**Step level** ÔÇö per-step container config:\n    75Ôćĺ```\n    76Ôćĺstep code {\n    77Ôćĺ  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78Ôćĺ  container {\n    79Ôćĺ    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80Ôćĺ    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81Ôćĺ    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82Ôćĺ  }\n    83Ôćĺ  results = [success, fail]\n    84Ôćĺ}\n    85Ôćĺ```\n    86Ôćĺ\n    87Ôćĺ**Workflow level** ÔÇö defaults for all steps:\n    88Ôćĺ```\n    89Ôćĺworkflow \"develop\" {\n    90Ôćĺ  container {\n    91Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92Ôćĺ    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93Ôćĺ    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94Ôćĺ  }\n    95Ôćĺ  ...\n    96Ôćĺ}\n    97Ôćĺ```\n    98Ôćĺ\n    99ÔćĺSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100Ôćĺ\n   101Ôćĺ### The `host {}` Block\n   102Ôćĺ\n   103ÔćĺCan appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\n   104Ôćĺwith a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n   105Ôćĺ\n   106Ôćĺ```\n   107Ôćĺworkflow \"main\" {\n   108Ôćĺ  host {\n   109Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   110Ôćĺ  }\n   111Ôćĺ  ...\n   112Ôćĺ}\n   113Ôćĺ```\n   114Ôćĺ\n   115ÔćĺSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   116Ôćĺ`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n   117Ôćĺ\n   118Ôćĺ### Wiring Syntax\n   119Ôćĺ\n   120ÔćĺConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   121Ôćĺ\n   122Ôćĺ```\n   123Ôćĺimplement:success -> test\n   124Ôćĺimplement:fail -> abort\n   125Ôćĺtest:success -> done\n   126Ôćĺtest:fail -> fix\n   127Ôćĺ```\n   128Ôćĺ\n   129Ôćĺ### Wire Output Mappings\n   130Ôćĺ\n   131ÔćĺExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   132Ôćĺ\n   133Ôćĺ```\n   134Ôćĺstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135Ôćĺ```\n   136Ôćĺ\n   137ÔćĺPath expressions:\n   138Ôćĺ\n   139Ôćĺ| Expression | Meaning |\n   140Ôćĺ|---|---|\n   141Ôćĺ| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   142Ôćĺ| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   143Ôćĺ| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   144Ôćĺ| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   145Ôćĺ| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   146Ôćĺ\n   147ÔćĺIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   148Ôćĺtext, only bare `output` works.\n   149Ôćĺ\n   150Ôćĺ### Retry Loops\n   151Ôćĺ\n   152ÔćĺWire failures back to earlier steps:\n   153Ôćĺ\n   154Ôćĺ```\n   155Ôćĺtest:fail -> fix\n   156Ôćĺfix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   157Ôćĺfix:fail -> abort\n   158Ôćĺ```\n   159Ôćĺ\n   160ÔćĺUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   161Ôćĺ\n   162Ôćĺ```\n   163Ôćĺstep fix {\n   164Ôćĺ  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   165Ôćĺ  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   166Ôćĺ  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   167Ôćĺ}\n   168Ôćĺ```\n   169Ôćĺ\n   170Ôćĺ### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   171Ôćĺ\n   172ÔćĺWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   173Ôćĺ\n   174Ôćĺ```\n   175Ôćĺtest:success -> lint\n   176Ôćĺtest:success -> quality\n   177Ôćĺ```\n   178Ôćĺ\n   179Ôćĺ### Collect (Join)\n   180Ôćĺ\n   181ÔćĺSynchronize parallel branches:\n   182Ôćĺ\n   183Ôćĺ```\n   184Ôćĺcollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   185Ôćĺcollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   186Ôćĺ```\n   187Ôćĺ\n   188Ôćĺ`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   189Ôćĺ\n   190Ôćĺ### Comments\n   191Ôćĺ\n   192ÔćĺLine comments with `//`:\n   193Ôćĺ\n   194Ôćĺ```\n   195Ôćĺ// This is a comment\n   196Ôćĺimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   197Ôćĺ```\n   198Ôćĺ\n   199Ôćĺ## Result Protocol\n   200Ôćĺ\n   201ÔćĺSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   202Ôćĺ\n   203Ôćĺ```\n   204ÔćĺCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   205Ôćĺ```\n   206Ôćĺ\n   207ÔćĺFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   208Ôćĺ\n   209ÔćĺRules:\n   210Ôćĺ- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   211Ôćĺ- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   212Ôćĺ- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   213Ôćĺ- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   214Ôćĺ- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   215Ôćĺ\n   216Ôćĺ## Prompt Assembly\n   217Ôćĺ\n   218ÔćĺWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   219Ôćĺ\n   220Ôćĺ1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   221Ôćĺ2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   222Ôćĺ3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   223Ôćĺ4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   224Ôćĺ\n   225ÔćĺThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   226Ôćĺ\n   227Ôćĺ## Agent Command Resolution\n   228Ôćĺ\n   229ÔćĺPriority (highest to lowest):\n   230Ôćĺ1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   231Ôćĺ2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n   232Ôćĺ3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   233Ôćĺ4. Default: `claude`\n   234Ôćĺ\n   235Ôćĺ### Fallback Chains\n   236Ôćĺ\n   237ÔćĺComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   238Ôćĺ\n   239Ôćĺ```\n   240Ôćĺagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   241Ôćĺ```\n   242Ôćĺ\n   243Ôćĺ- **Command not found / failed to start** ÔÇö try next command\n   244Ôćĺ- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö try next command\n   245Ôćĺ- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö use that result (no fallback)\n   246Ôćĺ- **Exit 0** ÔÇö use result (no fallback)\n   247Ôćĺ- **All commands fail to start** ÔÇö step returns an error\n   248Ôćĺ- **Last command crashes without marker** ÔÇö step returns `fail`\n   249Ôćĺ\n   250ÔćĺKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n   251Ôćĺ\n   252Ôćĺ## Workflow Locations\n   253Ôćĺ\n   254Ôćĺ**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   255Ôćĺvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   256Ôćĺ\n   257Ôćĺ**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   258ÔćĺSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   259Ôćĺdispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n   260Ôćĺexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n   261Ôćĺfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n   262Ôćĺ\n   263ÔćĺA single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\n   264Ôćĺuses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n   265Ôćĺ\n   266Ôćĺ| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n   267Ôćĺ|-------|--------------|---------|\n   268Ôćĺ| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n   269Ôćĺ| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n   270Ôćĺ| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n   271Ôćĺ\n   272ÔćĺOnly `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\n   273Ôćĺmode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n   274Ôćĺ\n   275Ôćĺ### list-tasks Output Format\n   276Ôćĺ\n   277ÔćĺThe `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\n   278Ôćĺobject:\n   279Ôćĺ\n   280Ôćĺ| Field | Required | Description |\n   281Ôćĺ|-------|----------|-------------|\n   282Ôćĺ| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n   283Ôćĺ| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n   284Ôćĺ| `title` | no | Short summary |\n   285Ôćĺ| `description` | no | Full description |\n   286Ôćĺ| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n   287Ôćĺ\n   288ÔćĺThe daemon picks the first task with status `open`, runs `main` with that task's ID\n   289Ôćĺset in `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, then runs `finalize` with the outcome. Tasks are\n   290Ôćĺdeduplicated within a timeout window to prevent rapid reassignment of the same task.\n   291Ôćĺ\n   292Ôćĺ### Host Workflow Example\n   293Ôćĺ\n   294ÔćĺA three-phase `host.cloche`:\n   295Ôćĺ\n   296Ôćĺ```\n   297Ôćĺworkflow \"list-tasks\" {\n   298Ôćĺ  step fetch-tickets {\n   299Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n   300Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   301Ôćĺ  }\n   302Ôćĺ\n   303Ôćĺ  fetch-tickets:success -> done\n   304Ôćĺ  fetch-tickets:fail    -> abort\n   305Ôćĺ}\n   306Ôćĺ\n   307Ôćĺworkflow \"main\" {\n   308Ôćĺ  host {\n   309Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   310Ôćĺ  }\n   311Ôćĺ\n   312Ôćĺ  step prepare-prompt {\n   313Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   314Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   315Ôćĺ  }\n   316Ôćĺ\n   317Ôćĺ  step develop {\n   318Ôćĺ    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   319Ôćĺ    results       = [success, fail]\n   320Ôćĺ  }\n   321Ôćĺ\n   322Ôćĺ  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n   323Ôćĺ  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   324Ôćĺ  develop:success        -> done\n   325Ôćĺ  develop:fail           -> done\n   326Ôćĺ}\n   327Ôćĺ\n   328Ôćĺworkflow \"finalize\" {\n   329Ôćĺ  step push-for-review {\n   330Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n   331Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   332Ôćĺ  }\n   333Ôćĺ\n   334Ôćĺ  push-for-review:success -> done\n   335Ôćĺ  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n   336Ôćĺ}\n   337Ôćĺ```\n   338Ôćĺ\n   339ÔćĺThe `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\n   340Ôćĺreceives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket. The `finalize`\n   341Ôćĺworkflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\n   342Ôćĺwhat cleanup to perform.\n   343Ôćĺ\n   344Ôćĺ### Host Step Environment Variables\n   345Ôćĺ\n   346Ôćĺ| Variable | Description |\n   347Ôćĺ|----------|-------------|\n   348Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n   349Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n   350Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n   351Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   352Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID assigned by the daemon (set for `main` and `finalize` phases). |\n   353Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` | Result of the `main` workflow (`succeeded` or `failed`). Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   354Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` | Run ID of the completed `main` workflow. Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   355Ôćĺ| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings. |\n   356Ôćĺ\n   357Ôćĺ### Container Environment Variables\n   358Ôćĺ\n   359Ôćĺ| Variable | Description |\n   360Ôćĺ|----------|-------------|\n   361Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   362Ôćĺ| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n   363Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n   364Ôćĺ\n   365Ôćĺ## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n   366Ôćĺ\n   367Ôćĺ```\n   368Ôćĺworkflow \"develop\" {\n   369Ôćĺ  step implement {\n   370Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n   371Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   372Ôćĺ  }\n   373Ôćĺ\n   374Ôćĺ  step test {\n   375Ôćĺ    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n   376Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   377Ôćĺ  }\n   378Ôćĺ\n   379Ôćĺ  step lint {\n   380Ôćĺ    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n   381Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   382Ôćĺ  }\n   383Ôćĺ\n   384Ôćĺ  step quality {\n   385Ôćĺ    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n   386Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   387Ôćĺ  }\n   388Ôćĺ\n   389Ôćĺ  step fix {\n   390Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n   391Ôćĺ    max_attempts = \"2\"\n   392Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   393Ôćĺ  }\n   394Ôćĺ\n   395Ôćĺ  implement:success -> test\n   396Ôćĺ  implement:fail -> abort\n   397Ôćĺ\n   398Ôćĺ  test:success -> lint\n   399Ôćĺ  test:success -> quality\n   400Ôćĺ  test:fail -> fix\n   401Ôćĺ\n   402Ôćĺ  lint:fail -> fix\n   403Ôćĺ  quality:fail -> fix\n   404Ôćĺ  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   405Ôćĺ\n   406Ôćĺ  fix:success -> test\n   407Ôćĺ  fix:fail -> abort\n   408Ôćĺ  fix:give-up -> abort\n   409Ôćĺ}\n   410Ôćĺ```\n   411Ôćĺ\n   412Ôćĺ## Container Isolation Model\n   413Ôćĺ\n   414Ôćĺ- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n   415Ôćĺ- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n   416Ôćĺ- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n   417Ôćĺ- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n   418Ôćĺ- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n   419Ôćĺ\n   420ÔćĺYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n   421Ôćĺ\n   422Ôćĺ## CLI Reference\n   423Ôćĺ\n   424Ôćĺ### `cloche init`\n   425Ôćĺ\n   426ÔćĺScaffold a new Cloche project.\n   427Ôćĺ\n   428Ôćĺ```\n   429Ôćĺcloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n   430Ôćĺ```\n   431Ôćĺ\n   432Ôćĺ| Flag | Default | Description |\n   433Ôćĺ|------|---------|-------------|\n   434Ôćĺ| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   435Ôćĺ| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n   436Ôćĺ\n   437ÔćĺCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n   438Ôćĺhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n   439Ôćĺ\n   440Ôćĺ### `cloche run`\n   441Ôćĺ\n   442ÔćĺLaunch a workflow run.\n   443Ôćĺ\n   444Ôćĺ```\n   445Ôćĺcloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n   446Ôćĺ```\n   447Ôćĺ\n   448Ôćĺ| Flag | Description |\n   449Ôćĺ|------|-------------|\n   450Ôćĺ| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   451Ôćĺ| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   452Ôćĺ| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   453Ôćĺ| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   454Ôćĺ\n   455ÔćĺMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   456Ôćĺwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   457Ôćĺ\n   458Ôćĺ### `cloche status`\n   459Ôćĺ\n   460Ôćĺ```\n   461Ôćĺcloche status <run-id>\n   462Ôćĺ```\n   463Ôćĺ\n   464ÔćĺShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   465Ôćĺ\n   466Ôćĺ### `cloche list`\n   467Ôćĺ\n   468Ôćĺ```\n   469Ôćĺcloche list [--all]\n   470Ôćĺ```\n   471Ôćĺ\n   472ÔćĺLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n   473Ôćĺ\n   474Ôćĺ### `cloche logs`\n   475Ôćĺ\n   476Ôćĺ```\n   477Ôćĺcloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n   478Ôćĺ```\n   479Ôćĺ\n   480Ôćĺ| Flag | Description |\n   481Ôćĺ|------|-------------|\n   482Ôćĺ| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   483Ôćĺ| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   484Ôćĺ| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   485Ôćĺ\n   486ÔćĺWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   487Ôćĺ\n   488Ôćĺ### `cloche poll`\n   489Ôćĺ\n   490Ôćĺ```\n   491Ôćĺcloche poll <run-id>\n   492Ôćĺ```\n   493Ôćĺ\n   494ÔćĺBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   495Ôćĺ\n   496Ôćĺ### `cloche stop`\n   497Ôćĺ\n   498Ôćĺ```\n   499Ôćĺcloche stop <run-id>\n   500Ôćĺ```\n   501Ôćĺ\n   502Ôćĺ### `cloche delete`\n   503Ôćĺ\n   504Ôćĺ```\n   505Ôćĺcloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   506Ôćĺ```\n   507Ôćĺ\n   508ÔćĺDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   509Ôćĺ\n   510Ôćĺ### `cloche health`\n   511Ôćĺ\n   512Ôćĺ```\n   513Ôćĺcloche health\n   514Ôćĺ```\n   515Ôćĺ\n   516ÔćĺShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   517Ôćĺ\n   518Ôćĺ### `cloche get`\n   519Ôćĺ\n   520Ôćĺ```\n   521Ôćĺcloche get <key>\n   522Ôćĺ```\n   523Ôćĺ\n   524ÔćĺGet a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   525Ôćĺthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   526Ôćĺthe current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n   527Ôćĺ\n   528Ôćĺ### `cloche set`\n   529Ôćĺ\n   530Ôćĺ```\n   531Ôćĺcloche set <key> <value>\n   532Ôćĺ```\n   533Ôćĺ\n   534ÔćĺSet a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   535Ôćĺthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   536Ôćĺthe current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\n   537Ôćĺ\n   538Ôćĺ### `cloche tasks`\n   539Ôćĺ\n   540Ôćĺ```\n   541Ôćĺcloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   542Ôćĺ```\n   543Ôćĺ\n   544ÔćĺShow the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays\n   545Ôćĺupcoming/open tasks, which tasks are assigned to which runs, and auto-assignment\n   546Ôćĺstate. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP` (talks to the daemon's web API).\n   547Ôćĺ\n   548Ôćĺ| Flag | Default | Description |\n   549Ôćĺ|------|---------|-------------|\n   550Ôćĺ| `--project <dir>` | current directory name | Project to query tasks for. |\n   551Ôćĺ\n   552Ôćĺ### `cloche shutdown`\n   553Ôćĺ\n   554Ôćĺ```\n   555Ôćĺcloche shutdown\n   556Ôćĺ```\n   557Ôćĺ\n   558Ôćĺ## Project Layout\n   559Ôćĺ\n   560Ôćĺ```\n   561Ôćĺmy-project/\n   562ÔćĺÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ .cloche/\n   563ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n   564ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n   565ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n   566ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ config.toml           # Project configuration\n   567ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompts/              # Prompt templates\n   568ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ implement.md\n   569ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ fix.md\n   570ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ update-docs.md\n   571ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n   572ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n   573ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n   574ÔćĺÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n   575ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompt.txt        # User prompt\n   576ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ context.json      # Shared key-value store (cloche get/set)\n   577ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ output/\n   578ÔćĺÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ full.log      # Unified log\n   579ÔćĺÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ test.log      # Per-step script output\n   580ÔćĺÔöé       Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n   581ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n   582ÔćĺÔöé       ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ history.log       # Step execution log\n   583ÔćĺÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n   584ÔćĺÔööÔöÇÔöÇ .git/\n   585Ôćĺ```\n   586Ôćĺ\n   587Ôćĺ## Daemon Configuration\n   588Ôćĺ\n   589Ôćĺ| Variable | Default | Description |\n   590Ôćĺ|----------|---------|-------------|\n   591Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   592Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   593Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   594Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   595Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   596Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   597Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   598Ôćĺ| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   599Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   600Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   601Ôćĺ\n   602Ôćĺ### Client Configuration\n   603Ôćĺ\n   604Ôćĺ| Variable | Default | Description |\n   605Ôćĺ|----------|---------|-------------|\n   606Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   607Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   608Ôćĺ\n   609Ôćĺ## Dockerfile Requirements\n   610Ôćĺ\n   611ÔćĺThe container image must have:\n   612Ôćĺ- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   613Ôćĺ- `git` installed\n   614Ôćĺ- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   615Ôćĺ- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   616Ôćĺ- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   617Ôćĺ\n   618Ôćĺ## Build Commands\n   619Ôćĺ\n   620Ôćĺ```\n   621Ôćĺmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   622Ôćĺmake test           # Run all tests\n   623Ôćĺmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   624Ôćĺmake lint           # Run go vet\n   625Ôćĺmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   626Ôćĺmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   627Ôćĺmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   628Ôćĺmake clean          # Remove bin/\n   629Ôćĺ```\n   630Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"221369ce-d654-4cd4-877a-e329688c1fa8","uuid":"6f60bca7-5d4f-4b01-bbe3-c560d8aea6c6","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"# Cloche Usage\n\nCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\nworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\ncontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\nresults to a git branch.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\ndeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\nno orphans, entry point exists).\n\n### Minimal Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n### Step Configuration\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n\nA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n\n### The `file()` Function\n\n`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\ntemplates:\n\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n\n### The `container {}` Block\n\nCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n\n**Step level** ÔÇö per-step container config:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow level** ÔÇö defaults for all steps:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n\n### The `host {}` Block\n\nCan appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\nwith a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n\n### Wiring Syntax\n\nConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\n```\n\n### Wire Output Mappings\n\nExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\nPath expressions:\n\n| Expression | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n\nIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\ntext, only bare `output` works.\n\n### Retry Loops\n\nWire failures back to earlier steps:\n\n```\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test    // retry the test\nfix:fail -> abort\n```\n\nUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n\n```\nstep fix {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n  max_attempts = \"2\"\n  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n\nWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n\n```\ntest:success -> lint\ntest:success -> quality\n```\n\n### Collect (Join)\n\nSynchronize parallel branches:\n\n```\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\ncollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n\n### Comments\n\nLine comments with `//`:\n\n```\n// This is a comment\nimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n```\n\n## Result Protocol\n\nSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\nFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n\nRules:\n- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n\n## Prompt Assembly\n\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n\n1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n\nThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n\n## Agent Command Resolution\n\nPriority (highest to lowest):\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default: `claude`\n\n### Fallback Chains\n\nComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n\n```\nagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n```\n\n- **Command not found / failed to start** ÔÇö try next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö try next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** ÔÇö use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** ÔÇö step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** ÔÇö step returns `fail`\n\nKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n\n## Workflow Locations\n\n**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\nvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n\n**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\nSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\ndispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\nexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\nfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n\nA single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\nuses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n\n| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n|-------|--------------|---------|\n| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n\nOnly `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\nmode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n\n### list-tasks Output Format\n\nThe `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\nobject:\n\n| Field | Required | Description |\n|-------|----------|-------------|\n| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n| `title` | no | Short summary |\n| `description` | no | Full description |\n| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n\nThe daemon picks the first task with status `open`, runs `main` with that task's ID\nset in `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, then runs `finalize` with the outcome. Tasks are\ndeduplicated within a timeout window to prevent rapid reassignment of the same task.\n\n### Host Workflow Example\n\nA three-phase `host.cloche`:\n\n```\nworkflow \"list-tasks\" {\n  step fetch-tickets {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  fetch-tickets:success -> done\n  fetch-tickets:fail    -> abort\n}\n\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n\nworkflow \"finalize\" {\n  step push-for-review {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  push-for-review:success -> done\n  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n}\n```\n\nThe `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\nreceives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket. The `finalize`\nworkflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\nwhat cleanup to perform.\n\n### Host Step Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID assigned by the daemon (set for `main` and `finalize` phases). |\n| `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` | Result of the `main` workflow (`succeeded` or `failed`). Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n| `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` | Run ID of the completed `main` workflow. Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings. |\n\n### Container Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n\n## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step lint {\n    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step quality {\n    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n\n  test:success -> lint\n  test:success -> quality\n  test:fail -> fix\n\n  lint:fail -> fix\n  quality:fail -> fix\n  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n\n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n  fix:give-up -> abort\n}\n```\n\n## Container Isolation Model\n\n- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n\nYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n\n## CLI Reference\n\n### `cloche init`\n\nScaffold a new Cloche project.\n\n```\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n\nCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\nhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n\n### `cloche run`\n\nLaunch a workflow run.\n\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n\nMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\nwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [--all]\n```\n\nLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\nBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```\n\n### `cloche delete`\n\n```\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n```\n\nDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n\n### `cloche health`\n\n```\ncloche health\n```\n\nShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n\n### `cloche get`\n\n```\ncloche get <key>\n```\n\nGet a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\nthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\nthe current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n\n### `cloche set`\n\n```\ncloche set <key> <value>\n```\n\nSet a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\nthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\nthe current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\n\n### `cloche tasks`\n\n```\ncloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n```\n\nShow the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays\nupcoming/open tasks, which tasks are assigned to which runs, and auto-assignment\nstate. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP` (talks to the daemon's web API).\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--project <dir>` | current directory name | Project to query tasks for. |\n\n### `cloche shutdown`\n\n```\ncloche shutdown\n```\n\n## Project Layout\n\n```\nmy-project/\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ .cloche/\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ config.toml           # Project configuration\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompts/              # Prompt templates\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ implement.md\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ fix.md\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ update-docs.md\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompt.txt        # User prompt\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ context.json      # Shared key-value store (cloche get/set)\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ output/\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ full.log      # Unified log\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ test.log      # Per-step script output\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\nÔöé       ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ history.log       # Step execution log\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\nÔööÔöÇÔöÇ .git/\n```\n\n## Daemon Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n\n### Client Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n\n## Dockerfile Requirements\n\nThe container image must have:\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n\n## Build Commands\n\n```\nmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\nmake test           # Run all tests\nmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\nmake lint           # Run go vet\nmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\nmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\nmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\nmake clean          # Remove bin/\n```\n","numLines":630,"startLine":1,"totalLines":630}}}
