[2026-03-12T15:46:26Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01UpXAyfXDeG5grga281hJzv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014auqj9QFXx8yXLPX8SZUw7","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":742,"cache_read_input_tokens":20876,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":742,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kwo4Gqf8Kyz3LgA9JjACuj","session_id":"caefa047-41e4-4a64-a92e-dbea2379cd5a","uuid":"bbb56a72-87b3-43a9-8b44-693615f3deb7"}
[2026-03-12T15:46:26Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014auqj9QFXx8yXLPX8SZUw7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# Cloche Usage\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3ÔćĺCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4Ôćĺworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5Ôćĺcontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6Ôćĺresults to a git branch.\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8Ôćĺ## Core Concepts\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10Ôćĺ- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11Ôćĺ- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12Ôćĺ- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13Ôćĺ- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14Ôćĺ- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15Ôćĺ\n    16Ôćĺ## Workflow DSL\n    17Ôćĺ\n    18ÔćĺWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19Ôćĺdeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20Ôćĺno orphans, entry point exists).\n    21Ôćĺ\n    22Ôćĺ### Minimal Example\n    23Ôćĺ\n    24Ôćĺ```\n    25Ôćĺworkflow \"develop\" {\n    26Ôćĺ  step implement {\n    27Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    29Ôćĺ  }\n    30Ôćĺ\n    31Ôćĺ  step test {\n    32Ôćĺ    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n    34Ôćĺ  }\n    35Ôćĺ\n    36Ôćĺ  implement:success -> test\n    37Ôćĺ  implement:fail -> abort\n    38Ôćĺ  test:success -> done\n    39Ôćĺ  test:fail -> abort\n    40Ôćĺ}\n    41Ôćĺ```\n    42Ôćĺ\n    43Ôćĺ### Step Configuration\n    44Ôćĺ\n    45Ôćĺ| Key | Type | Description |\n    46Ôćĺ|-----|------|-------------|\n    47Ôćĺ| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48Ôćĺ| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49Ôćĺ| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50Ôćĺ| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51Ôćĺ| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52Ôćĺ| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53Ôćĺ| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54Ôćĺ| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55Ôćĺ| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56Ôćĺ| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57Ôćĺ\n    58ÔćĺA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59Ôćĺ\n    60Ôćĺ### The `file()` Function\n    61Ôćĺ\n    62Ôćĺ`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63Ôćĺ(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64Ôćĺtemplates:\n    65Ôćĺ\n    66Ôćĺ```\n    67Ôćĺprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68Ôćĺ```\n    69Ôćĺ\n    70Ôćĺ### The `container {}` Block\n    71Ôćĺ\n    72ÔćĺCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73Ôćĺ\n    74Ôćĺ**Step level** ÔÇö per-step container config:\n    75Ôćĺ```\n    76Ôćĺstep code {\n    77Ôćĺ  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78Ôćĺ  container {\n    79Ôćĺ    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80Ôćĺ    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81Ôćĺ    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82Ôćĺ  }\n    83Ôćĺ  results = [success, fail]\n    84Ôćĺ}\n    85Ôćĺ```\n    86Ôćĺ\n    87Ôćĺ**Workflow level** ÔÇö defaults for all steps:\n    88Ôćĺ```\n    89Ôćĺworkflow \"develop\" {\n    90Ôćĺ  container {\n    91Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92Ôćĺ    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93Ôćĺ    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94Ôćĺ  }\n    95Ôćĺ  ...\n    96Ôćĺ}\n    97Ôćĺ```\n    98Ôćĺ\n    99ÔćĺSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100Ôćĺ\n   101Ôćĺ### The `host {}` Block\n   102Ôćĺ\n   103ÔćĺCan appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\n   104Ôćĺwith a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n   105Ôćĺ\n   106Ôćĺ```\n   107Ôćĺworkflow \"main\" {\n   108Ôćĺ  host {\n   109Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   110Ôćĺ  }\n   111Ôćĺ  ...\n   112Ôćĺ}\n   113Ôćĺ```\n   114Ôćĺ\n   115ÔćĺSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   116Ôćĺ`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n   117Ôćĺ\n   118Ôćĺ### Wiring Syntax\n   119Ôćĺ\n   120ÔćĺConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   121Ôćĺ\n   122Ôćĺ```\n   123Ôćĺimplement:success -> test\n   124Ôćĺimplement:fail -> abort\n   125Ôćĺtest:success -> done\n   126Ôćĺtest:fail -> fix\n   127Ôćĺ```\n   128Ôćĺ\n   129Ôćĺ### Wire Output Mappings\n   130Ôćĺ\n   131ÔćĺExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   132Ôćĺ\n   133Ôćĺ```\n   134Ôćĺstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135Ôćĺ```\n   136Ôćĺ\n   137ÔćĺPath expressions:\n   138Ôćĺ\n   139Ôćĺ| Expression | Meaning |\n   140Ôćĺ|---|---|\n   141Ôćĺ| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   142Ôćĺ| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   143Ôćĺ| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   144Ôćĺ| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   145Ôćĺ| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   146Ôćĺ\n   147ÔćĺIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   148Ôćĺtext, only bare `output` works.\n   149Ôćĺ\n   150Ôćĺ### Retry Loops\n   151Ôćĺ\n   152ÔćĺWire failures back to earlier steps:\n   153Ôćĺ\n   154Ôćĺ```\n   155Ôćĺtest:fail -> fix\n   156Ôćĺfix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   157Ôćĺfix:fail -> abort\n   158Ôćĺ```\n   159Ôćĺ\n   160ÔćĺUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   161Ôćĺ\n   162Ôćĺ```\n   163Ôćĺstep fix {\n   164Ôćĺ  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   165Ôćĺ  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   166Ôćĺ  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   167Ôćĺ}\n   168Ôćĺ```\n   169Ôćĺ\n   170Ôćĺ### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   171Ôćĺ\n   172ÔćĺWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   173Ôćĺ\n   174Ôćĺ```\n   175Ôćĺtest:success -> lint\n   176Ôćĺtest:success -> quality\n   177Ôćĺ```\n   178Ôćĺ\n   179Ôćĺ### Collect (Join)\n   180Ôćĺ\n   181ÔćĺSynchronize parallel branches:\n   182Ôćĺ\n   183Ôćĺ```\n   184Ôćĺcollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   185Ôćĺcollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   186Ôćĺ```\n   187Ôćĺ\n   188Ôćĺ`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   189Ôćĺ\n   190Ôćĺ### Comments\n   191Ôćĺ\n   192ÔćĺLine comments with `//`:\n   193Ôćĺ\n   194Ôćĺ```\n   195Ôćĺ// This is a comment\n   196Ôćĺimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   197Ôćĺ```\n   198Ôćĺ\n   199Ôćĺ## Result Protocol\n   200Ôćĺ\n   201ÔćĺSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   202Ôćĺ\n   203Ôćĺ```\n   204ÔćĺCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   205Ôćĺ```\n   206Ôćĺ\n   207ÔćĺFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   208Ôćĺ\n   209ÔćĺRules:\n   210Ôćĺ- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   211Ôćĺ- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   212Ôćĺ- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   213Ôćĺ- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   214Ôćĺ- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   215Ôćĺ\n   216Ôćĺ## Prompt Assembly\n   217Ôćĺ\n   218ÔćĺWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   219Ôćĺ\n   220Ôćĺ1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   221Ôćĺ2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   222Ôćĺ3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   223Ôćĺ4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   224Ôćĺ\n   225ÔćĺThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   226Ôćĺ\n   227Ôćĺ## Agent Command Resolution\n   228Ôćĺ\n   229ÔćĺPriority (highest to lowest):\n   230Ôćĺ1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   231Ôćĺ2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n   232Ôćĺ3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   233Ôćĺ4. Default: `claude`\n   234Ôćĺ\n   235Ôćĺ### Fallback Chains\n   236Ôćĺ\n   237ÔćĺComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   238Ôćĺ\n   239Ôćĺ```\n   240Ôćĺagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   241Ôćĺ```\n   242Ôćĺ\n   243Ôćĺ- **Command not found / failed to start** ÔÇö try next command\n   244Ôćĺ- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö try next command\n   245Ôćĺ- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** ÔÇö use that result (no fallback)\n   246Ôćĺ- **Exit 0** ÔÇö use result (no fallback)\n   247Ôćĺ- **All commands fail to start** ÔÇö step returns an error\n   248Ôćĺ- **Last command crashes without marker** ÔÇö step returns `fail`\n   249Ôćĺ\n   250ÔćĺKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n   251Ôćĺ\n   252Ôćĺ## Workflow Locations\n   253Ôćĺ\n   254Ôćĺ**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   255Ôćĺvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   256Ôćĺ\n   257Ôćĺ**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   258ÔćĺSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   259Ôćĺdispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n   260Ôćĺexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n   261Ôćĺfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n   262Ôćĺ\n   263ÔćĺA single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\n   264Ôćĺuses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n   265Ôćĺ\n   266Ôćĺ| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n   267Ôćĺ|-------|--------------|---------|\n   268Ôćĺ| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n   269Ôćĺ| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n   270Ôćĺ| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n   271Ôćĺ\n   272ÔćĺOnly `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\n   273Ôćĺmode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n   274Ôćĺ\n   275Ôćĺ### list-tasks Output Format\n   276Ôćĺ\n   277ÔćĺThe `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\n   278Ôćĺobject:\n   279Ôćĺ\n   280Ôćĺ| Field | Required | Description |\n   281Ôćĺ|-------|----------|-------------|\n   282Ôćĺ| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n   283Ôćĺ| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n   284Ôćĺ| `title` | no | Short summary |\n   285Ôćĺ| `description` | no | Full description |\n   286Ôćĺ| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n   287Ôćĺ\n   288ÔćĺThe daemon picks the first task with status `open`, runs `main` with that task's ID\n   289Ôćĺset in `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, then runs `finalize` with the outcome. Tasks are\n   290Ôćĺdeduplicated within a timeout window to prevent rapid reassignment of the same task.\n   291Ôćĺ\n   292Ôćĺ### Host Workflow Example\n   293Ôćĺ\n   294ÔćĺA three-phase `host.cloche`:\n   295Ôćĺ\n   296Ôćĺ```\n   297Ôćĺworkflow \"list-tasks\" {\n   298Ôćĺ  step fetch-tickets {\n   299Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n   300Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   301Ôćĺ  }\n   302Ôćĺ\n   303Ôćĺ  fetch-tickets:success -> done\n   304Ôćĺ  fetch-tickets:fail    -> abort\n   305Ôćĺ}\n   306Ôćĺ\n   307Ôćĺworkflow \"main\" {\n   308Ôćĺ  host {\n   309Ôćĺ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   310Ôćĺ  }\n   311Ôćĺ\n   312Ôćĺ  step prepare-prompt {\n   313Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   314Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   315Ôćĺ  }\n   316Ôćĺ\n   317Ôćĺ  step develop {\n   318Ôćĺ    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   319Ôćĺ    results       = [success, fail]\n   320Ôćĺ  }\n   321Ôćĺ\n   322Ôćĺ  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n   323Ôćĺ  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   324Ôćĺ  develop:success        -> done\n   325Ôćĺ  develop:fail           -> done\n   326Ôćĺ}\n   327Ôćĺ\n   328Ôćĺworkflow \"finalize\" {\n   329Ôćĺ  step push-for-review {\n   330Ôćĺ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n   331Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   332Ôćĺ  }\n   333Ôćĺ\n   334Ôćĺ  push-for-review:success -> done\n   335Ôćĺ  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n   336Ôćĺ}\n   337Ôćĺ```\n   338Ôćĺ\n   339ÔćĺThe `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\n   340Ôćĺreceives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket. The `finalize`\n   341Ôćĺworkflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\n   342Ôćĺwhat cleanup to perform.\n   343Ôćĺ\n   344Ôćĺ### Host Step Environment Variables\n   345Ôćĺ\n   346Ôćĺ| Variable | Description |\n   347Ôćĺ|----------|-------------|\n   348Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n   349Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n   350Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n   351Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   352Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID assigned by the daemon (set for `main` and `finalize` phases). |\n   353Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` | Result of the `main` workflow (`succeeded` or `failed`). Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   354Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` | Run ID of the completed `main` workflow. Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   355Ôćĺ| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings. |\n   356Ôćĺ\n   357Ôćĺ### Container Environment Variables\n   358Ôćĺ\n   359Ôćĺ| Variable | Description |\n   360Ôćĺ|----------|-------------|\n   361Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   362Ôćĺ| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n   363Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n   364Ôćĺ\n   365Ôćĺ## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n   366Ôćĺ\n   367Ôćĺ```\n   368Ôćĺworkflow \"develop\" {\n   369Ôćĺ  step implement {\n   370Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n   371Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   372Ôćĺ  }\n   373Ôćĺ\n   374Ôćĺ  step test {\n   375Ôćĺ    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n   376Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   377Ôćĺ  }\n   378Ôćĺ\n   379Ôćĺ  step lint {\n   380Ôćĺ    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n   381Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   382Ôćĺ  }\n   383Ôćĺ\n   384Ôćĺ  step quality {\n   385Ôćĺ    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n   386Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail]\n   387Ôćĺ  }\n   388Ôćĺ\n   389Ôćĺ  step fix {\n   390Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n   391Ôćĺ    max_attempts = \"2\"\n   392Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   393Ôćĺ  }\n   394Ôćĺ\n   395Ôćĺ  implement:success -> test\n   396Ôćĺ  implement:fail -> abort\n   397Ôćĺ\n   398Ôćĺ  test:success -> lint\n   399Ôćĺ  test:success -> quality\n   400Ôćĺ  test:fail -> fix\n   401Ôćĺ\n   402Ôćĺ  lint:fail -> fix\n   403Ôćĺ  quality:fail -> fix\n   404Ôćĺ  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   405Ôćĺ\n   406Ôćĺ  fix:success -> test\n   407Ôćĺ  fix:fail -> abort\n   408Ôćĺ  fix:give-up -> abort\n   409Ôćĺ}\n   410Ôćĺ```\n   411Ôćĺ\n   412Ôćĺ## Container Isolation Model\n   413Ôćĺ\n   414Ôćĺ- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n   415Ôćĺ- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n   416Ôćĺ- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n   417Ôćĺ- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n   418Ôćĺ- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n   419Ôćĺ\n   420ÔćĺYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n   421Ôćĺ\n   422Ôćĺ## CLI Reference\n   423Ôćĺ\n   424Ôćĺ### `cloche init`\n   425Ôćĺ\n   426ÔćĺScaffold a new Cloche project.\n   427Ôćĺ\n   428Ôćĺ```\n   429Ôćĺcloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n   430Ôćĺ```\n   431Ôćĺ\n   432Ôćĺ| Flag | Default | Description |\n   433Ôćĺ|------|---------|-------------|\n   434Ôćĺ| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   435Ôćĺ| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n   436Ôćĺ\n   437ÔćĺCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n   438Ôćĺhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n   439Ôćĺ\n   440Ôćĺ### `cloche run`\n   441Ôćĺ\n   442ÔćĺLaunch a workflow run.\n   443Ôćĺ\n   444Ôćĺ```\n   445Ôćĺcloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n   446Ôćĺ```\n   447Ôćĺ\n   448Ôćĺ| Flag | Description |\n   449Ôćĺ|------|-------------|\n   450Ôćĺ| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   451Ôćĺ| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   452Ôćĺ| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   453Ôćĺ| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   454Ôćĺ\n   455ÔćĺMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   456Ôćĺwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   457Ôćĺ\n   458Ôćĺ### `cloche status`\n   459Ôćĺ\n   460Ôćĺ```\n   461Ôćĺcloche status <run-id>\n   462Ôćĺ```\n   463Ôćĺ\n   464ÔćĺShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   465Ôćĺ\n   466Ôćĺ### `cloche list`\n   467Ôćĺ\n   468Ôćĺ```\n   469Ôćĺcloche list [--all]\n   470Ôćĺ```\n   471Ôćĺ\n   472ÔćĺLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n   473Ôćĺ\n   474Ôćĺ### `cloche logs`\n   475Ôćĺ\n   476Ôćĺ```\n   477Ôćĺcloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n   478Ôćĺ```\n   479Ôćĺ\n   480Ôćĺ| Flag | Description |\n   481Ôćĺ|------|-------------|\n   482Ôćĺ| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   483Ôćĺ| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   484Ôćĺ| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   485Ôćĺ\n   486ÔćĺWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   487Ôćĺ\n   488Ôćĺ### `cloche poll`\n   489Ôćĺ\n   490Ôćĺ```\n   491Ôćĺcloche poll <run-id>\n   492Ôćĺ```\n   493Ôćĺ\n   494ÔćĺBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   495Ôćĺ\n   496Ôćĺ### `cloche stop`\n   497Ôćĺ\n   498Ôćĺ```\n   499Ôćĺcloche stop <run-id>\n   500Ôćĺ```\n   501Ôćĺ\n   502Ôćĺ### `cloche delete`\n   503Ôćĺ\n   504Ôćĺ```\n   505Ôćĺcloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   506Ôćĺ```\n   507Ôćĺ\n   508ÔćĺDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   509Ôćĺ\n   510Ôćĺ### `cloche health`\n   511Ôćĺ\n   512Ôćĺ```\n   513Ôćĺcloche health\n   514Ôćĺ```\n   515Ôćĺ\n   516ÔćĺShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   517Ôćĺ\n   518Ôćĺ### `cloche get`\n   519Ôćĺ\n   520Ôćĺ```\n   521Ôćĺcloche get <key>\n   522Ôćĺ```\n   523Ôćĺ\n   524ÔćĺGet a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   525Ôćĺthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   526Ôćĺthe current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n   527Ôćĺ\n   528Ôćĺ### `cloche set`\n   529Ôćĺ\n   530Ôćĺ```\n   531Ôćĺcloche set <key> <value>\n   532Ôćĺ```\n   533Ôćĺ\n   534ÔćĺSet a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   535Ôćĺthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   536Ôćĺthe current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\n   537Ôćĺ\n   538Ôćĺ### `cloche tasks`\n   539Ôćĺ\n   540Ôćĺ```\n   541Ôćĺcloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   542Ôćĺ```\n   543Ôćĺ\n   544ÔćĺShow the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays\n   545Ôćĺupcoming/open tasks, which tasks are assigned to which runs, and auto-assignment\n   546Ôćĺstate. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP` (talks to the daemon's web API).\n   547Ôćĺ\n   548Ôćĺ| Flag | Default | Description |\n   549Ôćĺ|------|---------|-------------|\n   550Ôćĺ| `--project <dir>` | current directory name | Project to query tasks for. |\n   551Ôćĺ\n   552Ôćĺ### `cloche shutdown`\n   553Ôćĺ\n   554Ôćĺ```\n   555Ôćĺcloche shutdown\n   556Ôćĺ```\n   557Ôćĺ\n   558Ôćĺ## Project Layout\n   559Ôćĺ\n   560Ôćĺ```\n   561Ôćĺmy-project/\n   562ÔćĺÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ .cloche/\n   563ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n   564ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n   565ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n   566ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ config.toml           # Project configuration\n   567ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompts/              # Prompt templates\n   568ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ implement.md\n   569ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ fix.md\n   570ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ update-docs.md\n   571ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n   572ÔćĺÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n   573ÔćĺÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n   574ÔćĺÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n   575ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompt.txt        # User prompt\n   576ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ context.json      # Shared key-value store (cloche get/set)\n   577ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ output/\n   578ÔćĺÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ full.log      # Unified log\n   579ÔćĺÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ test.log      # Per-step script output\n   580ÔćĺÔöé       Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n   581ÔćĺÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n   582ÔćĺÔöé       ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ history.log       # Step execution log\n   583ÔćĺÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n   584ÔćĺÔööÔöÇÔöÇ .git/\n   585Ôćĺ```\n   586Ôćĺ\n   587Ôćĺ## Daemon Configuration\n   588Ôćĺ\n   589Ôćĺ| Variable | Default | Description |\n   590Ôćĺ|----------|---------|-------------|\n   591Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   592Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   593Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   594Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   595Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   596Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   597Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   598Ôćĺ| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   599Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   600Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   601Ôćĺ\n   602Ôćĺ### Client Configuration\n   603Ôćĺ\n   604Ôćĺ| Variable | Default | Description |\n   605Ôćĺ|----------|---------|-------------|\n   606Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   607Ôćĺ| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   608Ôćĺ\n   609Ôćĺ## Dockerfile Requirements\n   610Ôćĺ\n   611ÔćĺThe container image must have:\n   612Ôćĺ- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   613Ôćĺ- `git` installed\n   614Ôćĺ- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   615Ôćĺ- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   616Ôćĺ- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   617Ôćĺ\n   618Ôćĺ## Build Commands\n   619Ôćĺ\n   620Ôćĺ```\n   621Ôćĺmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   622Ôćĺmake test           # Run all tests\n   623Ôćĺmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   624Ôćĺmake lint           # Run go vet\n   625Ôćĺmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   626Ôćĺmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   627Ôćĺmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   628Ôćĺmake clean          # Remove bin/\n   629Ôćĺ```\n   630Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kwo4Gqf8Kyz3LgA9JjACuj","session_id":"caefa047-41e4-4a64-a92e-dbea2379cd5a","uuid":"8aac2b52-f182-4e2b-9098-62e30b3e382d"}
