[2026-03-12T15:46:26Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01WYr8gUNzrEhCAGHTkwHx1k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LwjEndu437Fs5JFmpAhBNm","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1573,"cache_read_input_tokens":57198,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1573,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kwo4Gqf8Kyz3LgA9JjACuj","session_id":"caefa047-41e4-4a64-a92e-dbea2379cd5a","uuid":"6dc22e17-49ae-44ce-87ae-3d49d690ed59"}
[2026-03-12T15:46:26Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LwjEndu437Fs5JFmpAhBNm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# Cloche System Design\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3Ôćĺ## Overview\n     4Ôćĺ\n     5ÔćĺCloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     6Ôćĺenvironments for coding agents to operate in isolation, a workflow DSL for linking\n     7Ôćĺagentic and script-driven tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n     8Ôćĺ\n     9ÔćĺThis document describes the architecture for the MVP (v0.1).\n    10Ôćĺ\n    11Ôćĺ## System Components\n    12Ôćĺ\n    13ÔćĺCloche is a Go monorepo producing three binaries:\n    14Ôćĺ\n    15Ôćĺ```\n    16Ôćĺcmd/\n    17Ôćĺ  cloche/         # CLI client (short-lived)\n    18Ôćĺ  cloched/        # Daemon/orchestrator (long-running)\n    19Ôćĺ  cloche-agent/   # In-container entrypoint (autonomous)\n    20Ôćĺ```\n    21Ôćĺ\n    22Ôćĺ### cloche (CLI)\n    23Ôćĺ\n    24ÔćĺShort-lived process. Talks to `cloched` over gRPC (Unix socket locally, TCP remotely).\n    25Ôćĺ\n    26ÔćĺSubcommands:\n    27Ôćĺ- `run <workflow>` ÔÇö Launch a new workflow run\n    28Ôćĺ- `status [run-id]` ÔÇö Check run status\n    29Ôćĺ- `logs <run-id>` ÔÇö Stream logs from a running workflow (bidirectional gRPC stream)\n    30Ôćĺ- `stop <run-id>` ÔÇö Cancel a running workflow (signals container with SIGTERM)\n    31Ôćĺ\n    32ÔćĺAccepts prompt files or stdin input for user commands.\n    33Ôćĺ\n    34Ôćĺ### cloched (Daemon)\n    35Ôćĺ\n    36ÔćĺLong-running process. Responsibilities:\n    37Ôćĺ- Launch and manage Docker containers for workflow runs\n    38Ôćĺ- Listen to status streams from running agents\n    39Ôćĺ- Record captures (step inputs, outputs, results, logs)\n    40Ôćĺ- Expose gRPC API for the CLI\n    41Ôćĺ- Persist state via pluggable storage (SQLite initially)\n    42Ôćĺ\n    43ÔćĺThe daemon does NOT interpret workflow logic. It knows \"container X is running workflow Y\"\n    44Ôćĺand collects status. The agent is self-directing.\n    45Ôćĺ\n    46Ôćĺ### cloche-agent (In-Container Runtime)\n    47Ôćĺ\n    48ÔćĺAutonomous process running inside the Docker container. Responsibilities:\n    49Ôćĺ- Parse the workflow DSL (workflow files live in the codebase)\n    50Ôćĺ- Walk the workflow graph, executing steps and following results\n    51Ôćĺ- Invoke coding agents (Claude Code, custom commands) and scripts\n    52Ôćĺ- Stream structured status events back to `cloched`\n    53Ôćĺ- Run to completion (`done` or `abort`) without human intervention\n    54Ôćĺ\n    55ÔćĺThe agent is told which workflow to execute at launch. It handles everything else.\n    56Ôćĺ\n    57Ôćĺ## Communication\n    58Ôćĺ\n    59Ôćĺ### CLI <-> Daemon: gRPC\n    60Ôćĺ\n    61Ôćĺ- Protobuf contracts define the API (the API is the spec)\n    62Ôćĺ- Bidirectional streaming for `logs` (tail container output in real-time)\n    63Ôćĺ- Unix socket for local communication, TCP for remote\n    64Ôćĺ\n    65Ôćĺ### Agent <-> Daemon: Structured JSON over stdout\n    66Ôćĺ\n    67Ôćĺ- The agent writes JSON-lines to stdout with status updates\n    68Ôćĺ- `cloched` attaches to the container's stdout stream via Docker API\n    69Ôćĺ- Messages include: step started, step completed (with result name), logs, errors\n    70Ôćĺ- Kill/cancel: daemon sends SIGTERM to container, agent handles graceful shutdown\n    71Ôćĺ\n    72Ôćĺ## Workflow DSL\n    73Ôćĺ\n    74Ôćĺ### Vocabulary\n    75Ôćĺ\n    76Ôćĺ| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n    77Ôćĺ|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n    78Ôćĺ| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\n    79Ôćĺ| step     | A unit of work (type: `agent` or `script`)                         |\n    80Ôćĺ| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n    81Ôćĺ| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step                              |\n    82Ôćĺ| done     | Built-in terminal step indicating successful completion            |\n    83Ôćĺ| abort    | Built-in terminal step indicating failure (reports error and exits)|\n    84Ôćĺ\n    85Ôćĺ### Syntax\n    86Ôćĺ\n    87Ôćĺ```\n    88Ôćĺworkflow \"implement-feature\" {\n    89Ôćĺ  step code {\n    90Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    91Ôćĺ    container {\n    92Ôćĺ      image = \"cloche/agent:latest\"\n    93Ôćĺ      network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"internal-docs.company.com\"]\n    94Ôćĺ    }\n    95Ôćĺ    results = [success, fail, retry_with_feedback]\n    96Ôćĺ  }\n    97Ôćĺ\n    98Ôćĺ  step check {\n    99Ôćĺ    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n   100Ôćĺ    results = [pass, fail]\n   101Ôćĺ  }\n   102Ôćĺ\n   103Ôćĺ  step review {\n   104Ôćĺ    prompt = file(\"prompts/review.md\")\n   105Ôćĺ    input = step.code.output\n   106Ôćĺ    results = [approved, changes_requested]\n   107Ôćĺ  }\n   108Ôćĺ\n   109Ôćĺ  code:success -> check\n   110Ôćĺ  code:fail -> abort\n   111Ôćĺ  code:retry_with_feedback -> code\n   112Ôćĺ\n   113Ôćĺ  check:pass -> review\n   114Ôćĺ  check:fail -> code:retry_with_feedback\n   115Ôćĺ\n   116Ôćĺ  review:approved -> done\n   117Ôćĺ  review:changes_requested -> code\n   118Ôćĺ}\n   119Ôćĺ```\n   120Ôćĺ\n   121Ôćĺ### Key Properties\n   122Ôćĺ\n   123Ôćĺ- Step type is inferred from content: `prompt` field Ôćĺ agent step, `run` field Ôćĺ script step.\n   124Ôćĺ- Steps declare which results they can emit. The step decides at runtime which result to report.\n   125Ôćĺ- Wiring is separate from step definitions. This enables runtime injection of new steps\n   126Ôćĺ  (the self-evolution feature) ÔÇö insert a new check between existing steps by rewiring,\n   127Ôćĺ  without modifying either step.\n   128Ôćĺ- `file()` loads external content (prompt files, scripts).\n   129Ôćĺ- Step inputs can reference other step outputs (`step.code.output`).\n   130Ôćĺ- The graph engine validates at parse time: all declared results are wired, no orphan steps,\n   131Ôćĺ  entry point exists.\n   132Ôćĺ\n   133Ôćĺ## Hexagonal Architecture\n   134Ôćĺ\n   135ÔćĺThe core domain is independent of Docker, gRPC, SQLite, or any other infrastructure.\n   136Ôćĺ\n   137Ôćĺ### Domain\n   138Ôćĺ\n   139Ôćĺ```\n   140Ôćĺinternal/domain/\n   141Ôćĺ  workflow.go    # Workflow, Step, Result, Graph types\n   142Ôćĺ  run.go         # Run, RunState, StepExecution types\n   143Ôćĺ  capture.go     # CapturedInput, CapturedOutput for replay\n   144Ôćĺ```\n   145Ôćĺ\n   146Ôćĺ### Ports (interfaces)\n   147Ôćĺ\n   148Ôćĺ```\n   149Ôćĺinternal/ports/\n   150Ôćĺ  store.go       # RunStore, WorkflowStore, CaptureStore\n   151Ôćĺ  container.go   # ContainerRuntime (start, stop, attach, logs)\n   152Ôćĺ  agent.go       # AgentAdapter (how to invoke an agent)\n   153Ôćĺ  notifier.go    # StatusNotifier (how to report progress)\n   154Ôćĺ```\n   155Ôćĺ\n   156Ôćĺ### Adapters (implementations)\n   157Ôćĺ\n   158Ôćĺ```\n   159Ôćĺinternal/adapters/\n   160Ôćĺ  docker/        # ContainerRuntime via Docker API\n   161Ôćĺ  sqlite/        # Store implementations via SQLite\n   162Ôćĺ  grpc/          # gRPC server (daemon) and client (CLI)\n   163Ôćĺ  agents/\n   164Ôćĺ    claudecode/  # AgentAdapter for Claude Code\n   165Ôćĺ    generic/     # AgentAdapter for arbitrary commands\n   166Ôćĺ```\n   167Ôćĺ\n   168Ôćĺ### Key Interfaces\n   169Ôćĺ\n   170Ôćĺ- **ContainerRuntime** ÔÇö Start/stop containers, attach to stdout, copy files in/out.\n   171Ôćĺ  Docker today, Podman or Firecracker later.\n   172Ôćĺ- **RunStore** ÔÇö Persist run state (active step, reported results, timestamps).\n   173Ôćĺ- **CaptureStore** ÔÇö Store step inputs/outputs for replay. Git refs serve as pointers\n   174Ôćĺ  to file states; metadata lives in the store.\n   175Ôćĺ- **AgentAdapter** ÔÇö Translates between Cloche's step protocol and a specific agent's\n   176Ôćĺ  interface. Claude Code adapter knows how to invoke `claude` CLI. Generic adapter runs\n   177Ôćĺ  any command.\n   178Ôćĺ- **StatusNotifier** ÔÇö How the agent reports progress. Stdout JSON-lines initially.\n   179Ôćĺ\n   180Ôćĺ## Container Model\n   181Ôćĺ\n   182Ôćĺ### One Container Per Workflow Run\n   183Ôćĺ\n   184ÔćĺA container is spun up for a workflow run. All steps execute inside the same container.\n   185ÔćĺFile state accumulates naturally across steps (agent modifies code, then test script\n   186Ôćĺruns against those modifications).\n   187Ôćĺ\n   188Ôćĺ### Lifecycle\n   189Ôćĺ\n   190Ôćĺ1. `cloched` pulls/builds the container image\n   191Ôćĺ2. Copies project files into the container at `/workspace`\n   192Ôćĺ3. Starts the container with `cloche-agent` as entrypoint, passing the workflow name\n   193Ôćĺ4. `cloche-agent` parses the workflow, walks the graph, executes steps\n   194Ôćĺ5. Agent streams status events to `cloched` via stdout\n   195Ôćĺ6. At step boundaries, modified files are pushed to the host via git (agent-specific branch)\n   196Ôćĺ7. On completion (`done`/`abort`), container is stopped\n   197Ôćĺ\n   198Ôćĺ### File Extraction via Git\n   199Ôćĺ\n   200ÔćĺThe container's git remote is configured to push to the host repository. Each run pushes\n   201Ôćĺto a unique branch (e.g. `cloche/run-<id>/step-<name>`). This provides:\n   202Ôćĺ- Full git history of what the agent did\n   203Ôćĺ- Trivial diffs between input and output states\n   204Ôćĺ- Clean branch-per-step organization\n   205Ôćĺ- No bind mounts (maintains isolation)\n   206Ôćĺ\n   207Ôćĺ### Security Boundaries\n   208Ôćĺ\n   209Ôćĺ1. **Filesystem** ÔÇö No access beyond `/workspace`. Copy-in at start, git push for extraction.\n   210Ôćĺ2. **Network** ÔÇö `--network none` by default. If `network_allow` is specified, Cloche creates\n   211Ôćĺ   a custom Docker network restricting egress to allowlisted domains via DNS proxy.\n   212Ôćĺ3. **Environment** ÔÇö Configured in Dockerfile/image. Cloche does not inject env vars.\n   213Ôćĺ\n   214Ôćĺ## Capture System\n   215Ôćĺ\n   216ÔćĺEach step execution is captured for later inspection and replay.\n   217Ôćĺ\n   218Ôćĺ### What Gets Captured\n   219Ôćĺ\n   220Ôćĺ- Step config (prompt, type, container settings)\n   221Ôćĺ- Input state (git ref of what was provided to the step)\n   222Ôćĺ- Output state (git ref of what the step produced)\n   223Ôćĺ- Result reported (which result name)\n   224Ôćĺ- Stdout/stderr logs\n   225Ôćĺ- Timing metadata\n   226Ôćĺ\n   227Ôćĺ### Storage\n   228Ôćĺ\n   229ÔćĺMetadata in the store (SQLite initially). Git refs serve as pointers to actual file\n   230Ôćĺstates ÔÇö no duplication of file content.\n   231Ôćĺ\n   232Ôćĺ## MVP Scope (v0.1)\n   233Ôćĺ\n   234Ôćĺ### In Scope\n   235Ôćĺ\n   236Ôćĺ- `cloche` CLI: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`\n   237Ôćĺ- `cloched` daemon: container lifecycle, status collection, gRPC API, SQLite store\n   238Ôćĺ- `cloche-agent`: DSL parser, graph engine, agent/script execution, status reporting\n   239Ôćĺ- Workflow DSL: steps, results, wiring, `done`/`abort` terminals, `file()` references\n   240Ôćĺ- Container model: Docker, copy-in project files, git push for extraction, network allowlist\n   241Ôćĺ- Agent adapters: Generic (run a command) + Claude Code\n   242Ôćĺ- Capture system: Record step inputs/outputs/results\n   243Ôćĺ\n   244Ôćĺ### Post-MVP\n   245Ôćĺ\n   246Ôćĺ- Self-evolution: failure pattern analysis, automatic step injection into workflows\n   247Ôćĺ- Replay system: partial/full/dry replay of captured runs\n   248Ôćĺ- Auto-split commits into stacked branches\n   249Ôćĺ- Additional agent adapters\n   250Ôćĺ- Alternative storage backends (Postgres, DynamoDB)\n   251Ôćĺ- Alternative container runtimes (Podman, Firecracker)\n   252Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kwo4Gqf8Kyz3LgA9JjACuj","session_id":"caefa047-41e4-4a64-a92e-dbea2379cd5a","uuid":"18ca87c5-f1e7-4f6b-bd0f-0df6e0b1246c"}
