[2026-03-12T15:46:26Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kwo4Gqf8Kyz3LgA9JjACuj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have comprehensive information about the cloche codebase. Let me compile the complete findings into a detailed report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the cloche codebase and compiled all the details needed for a comprehensive getting-started guide. Here are the complete findings:\n\n---\n\n# CLOCHE GETTING-STARTED GUIDE ÔÇö RESEARCH FINDINGS\n\n## 1. BUILD/INSTALL\n\n**Build from Source:**\n- **Makefile targets:**\n  - `make build` Ôćĺ Builds all three binaries to `bin/` directory\n  - `make docker-build` Ôćĺ Builds the cloche-agent Docker image from `.cloche/Dockerfile`\n  - `make install PREFIX=~/.local` Ôćĺ Builds all binaries, builds Docker image, installs to prefix (default: `~/.local/bin/`), and starts daemon\n  - `make test` Ôćĺ Runs all tests\n  - `make test-short` Ôćĺ Runs tests, skipping slow ones\n  - `make lint` Ôćĺ Runs `go vet`\n  - `make proto` Ôćĺ Regenerates gRPC code from protobuf\n  - `make clean` Ôćĺ Removes `bin/` directory\n\n**Installation Methods:**\n- Build from source: `git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git && cd cloche && make install`\n- Via `go install`: `go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche@latest` (requires manual Docker image build)\n- Pre-built binaries: Planned but not yet available\n- Homebrew: Planned but not yet available\n- Docker daemon: Planned future option\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- Go 1.25+ (for building)\n- Docker (for running workflows)\n- Git (for result extraction via worktrees)\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` environment variable (for agent steps)\n\n**Installation Verification:**\n```bash\ncloche --help\ncloched --help\nmake docker-build\ncloche list\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. CLOCHE INIT COMMAND\n\n**Command Syntax:**\n```bash\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n```\n\n**Flags:**\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name; creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche` |\n| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for generated Dockerfile |\n\n**Files Created:**\nThe command scaffolds a `.cloche/` directory structure with these files (skips existing files):\n\n1. **`.cloche/<workflow>.cloche`** ÔÇö Container workflow definition (named after `--workflow` flag)\n2. **`.cloche/Dockerfile`** ÔÇö Container image definition\n3. **`.cloche/config.toml`** ÔÇö Project configuration with settings like `active`, `orchestration`, `evolution`\n4. **`.cloche/host.cloche`** ÔÇö Host orchestration workflow (runs on host machine)\n5. **`.cloche/prompts/implement.md`** ÔÇö Prompt template for implementation step\n6. **`.cloche/prompts/fix.md`** ÔÇö Prompt template for fixing failures\n7. **`.cloche/prompts/update-docs.md`** ÔÇö Prompt template for documentation updates\n8. **`.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh`** ÔÇö Bash script to generate prompts from task info\n9. **`.cloche/overrides/`** ÔÇö Directory for container-specific file overrides\n10. **`.cloche/version`** ÔÇö Version marker file\n\n**Directories Created:**\n- `.cloche/` ÔÇö Main configuration directory\n- `.cloche/prompts/` ÔÇö Prompt template directory\n- `.cloche/scripts/` ÔÇö Host-side script directory\n- `.cloche/overrides/` ÔÇö Container override files directory\n\n**Gitignore Modifications:**\nAdds patterns:\n- `.cloche/*-*-*/` ÔÇö Runtime directories (run IDs with hyphens)\n- `.cloche/run-*/` ÔÇö Legacy run directories\n- `.cloche/attempt_count/` ÔÇö Retry tracking\n- `.gitworktrees/` ÔÇö Git worktrees for result extraction\n\n**Post-Init Instructions Printed:**\n```\nNext steps:\n  1. Edit .cloche/config.toml ÔÇö set active = true to auto-run on startup\n  2. Edit .cloche/<workflow>.cloche ÔÇö adjust test command for your project\n  3. Edit .cloche/Dockerfile ÔÇö add your project's dependencies\n  4. Edit .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh ÔÇö customize prompt generation\n  5. Add container-specific overrides to .cloche/overrides/ (e.g. CLAUDE.md)\n  6. docker build -t cloche-agent -f .cloche/Dockerfile .\n  7. cloche run --workflow <workflow> --prompt \"...\"\n```\n\n**Requirement:** Must be run from inside a git repository.\n\n---\n\n## 3. DOCKERFILE CONFIGURATION\n\n**Template Location:** `.cloche/Dockerfile`\n\n**Generated Template Default:**\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\n\n# Add your project's dependencies here.\n# Example:\n#   RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n#   RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Base Image:** `cloche-base:latest` (default, customizable via `--base-image` flag)\n\n**Base Image Contents:**\nThe `cloche-base:latest` image includes:\n- Debian 12-slim base\n- `git` (for version control and commits)\n- `make` (for build commands)\n- `ca-certificates` (for HTTPS)\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- Non-root `agent` user\n- Working directory at `/workspace` owned by `agent`\n\n**Dockerfile Requirements (Must Have):**\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies\n- Any coding agents your workflow requires (e.g. `claude` CLI)\n\n**Example Customization (Ruby):**\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y ruby bundler\nRUN rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Example Customization (Go):**\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\nCOPY --from=golang:1.25 /usr/local/go /usr/local/go\nENV PATH=\"/usr/local/go/bin:${PATH}\"\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Example with Claude Code:**\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y nodejs npm\nRUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\nRUN rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Important:** The generated Dockerfile is a template. Customize it for your project's specific dependencies before running workflows.\n\n---\n\n## 4. WORKFLOW DSL SETUP\n\n**Workflow Files:** `.cloche/*.cloche` (container workflows) or `.cloche/host.cloche` (host workflows)\n\n**Syntax Overview:**\n```\nworkflow \"<name>\" {\n  step <step_name> {\n    prompt = file(\"path/to/prompt.md\")     # OR\n    run = \"shell command\"                  # OR\n    workflow_name = \"other-workflow\"       # (host only)\n    results = [result1, result2, ...]\n    [optional config]\n  }\n  \n  step1:result -> step2\n  step2:result -> done\n  step1:other -> abort\n}\n```\n\n**Step Types:**\n1. **Agent step** ÔÇö has `prompt` field; invokes a coding agent\n2. **Script step** ÔÇö has `run` field; executes a shell command\n3. **Workflow step** ÔÇö has `workflow_name` field; dispatches a container workflow (host only)\n\n**Result Declaration:**\nSteps declare their possible results: `results = [success, fail]` or `results = [success, fail, give-up]`\n\n**Wiring (Graph Edges):**\n- `step:result -> next_step` ÔÇö Route based on reported result\n- `step:result -> done` ÔÇö Success terminal\n- `step:result -> abort` ÔÇö Failure terminal\n- `collect all(step1:result, step2:result) -> done` ÔÇö Synchronize parallel branches\n\n**Built-in Terminals:**\n- `done` ÔÇö Successful completion\n- `abort` ÔÇö Failure/error completion\n\n**Key Configuration Options:**\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template for agent steps |\n| `run` | string | Shell command for script steps |\n| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch (host only) |\n| `results` | ident list | Declared result names |\n| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before auto `give-up` (e.g. `\"2\"`) |\n| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration (e.g. `\"30m\"`, default: 30m) |\n| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s); comma-separated for fallback chains (e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`) |\n| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments |\n| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include validation output in prompt |\n| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as prompt |\n\n**Container Configuration Block:**\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Wire Output Mappings:**\nExtract JSON values from step output and inject as environment variables:\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\n**Example Complete Workflow:**\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> fix\n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n  fix:give-up -> abort\n}\n```\n\n**Prompt Assembly (Agent Steps):**\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from:\n1. Step template content (from `prompt` field)\n2. User request (from `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`, prefixed with `## User Request`)\n3. Validation output (if `feedback = \"true\"`, from `.cloche/output/*.log` files)\n4. Result selection instructions (with possible results listed)\n\n**Result Protocol:**\nSteps report results by printing a marker to stdout:\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<result_name>\n```\nExamples: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:fail`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`\n\nFor script steps:\n- Exit 0 = `success`\n- Exit non-zero = `fail`\n\n**Comments:**\nUse `//` for line comments:\n```\nimplement:success -> test  // This is a comment\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. DOCUMENTATION POINTERS\n\n**Documentation Files Location:** `/workspace/docs/`\n\n### Available Documentation:\n\n1. **`docs/INSTALL.md`** ÔÇö Full installation guide\n   - Build from source\n   - `go install` method\n   - Pre-built binaries (planned)\n   - Homebrew (planned)\n   - Docker-only usage (planned)\n   - Verification steps\n   - Upgrade instructions\n\n2. **`docs/USAGE.md`** ÔÇö Complete CLI and usage reference (20KB)\n   - Core concepts\n   - Workflow DSL full syntax\n   - Step configuration options\n   - The `file()` function\n   - Container and host blocks\n   - Wiring syntax and output mappings\n   - Retry loops, parallel branches, collect/join\n   - Result protocol\n   - Prompt assembly\n   - Agent command resolution\n   - Complete example with parallel validation\n   - Container isolation model\n   - **CLI Reference:**\n     - `cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]`\n     - `cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]`\n     - `cloche status <run-id>`\n     - `cloche list [--all]`\n     - `cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]`\n     - `cloche poll <run-id>`\n     - `cloche stop <run-id>`\n     - `cloche delete <container-or-run-id>`\n     - `cloche health`\n     - `cloche get <key>`\n     - `cloche set <key> <value>`\n     - `cloche tasks [--project <dir>]`\n     - `cloche shutdown`\n   - Project layout\n   - Daemon configuration (environment variables)\n   - Client configuration\n   - Dockerfile requirements\n   - Build commands\n\n3. **`docs/workflows.md`** ÔÇö Workflow DSL reference (9KB)\n   - Workflow locations (container vs. host)\n   - DSL concepts\n   - Step types\n   - Syntax examples\n   - Key properties\n   - Wire output mappings\n   - Host block configuration\n   - Host workflow example with three phases\n   - Execution model\n\n4. **`docs/plans/`** ÔÇö Architecture and design documents\n   - `2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md` ÔÇö Complete system design and architecture\n   - `2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md` ÔÇö Implementation details\n   - `2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md` ÔÇö `cloche init` command design\n   - `2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md` ÔÇö Self-evolution feature\n   - `2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md` ÔÇö Base Docker image design\n   - `2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` ÔÇö Host workflow design\n   - And many others covering specific features\n\n### Project Layout Documentation:\n```\nmy-project/\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ .cloche/\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ config.toml           # Project configuration\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompts/              # Prompt templates\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ implement.md\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ fix.md\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ update-docs.md\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompt.txt        # User prompt\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ context.json      # Shared key-value store\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ output/\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ full.log      # Unified log\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ test.log      # Per-step script output\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ attempt_count/    # Retry counters\nÔöé       ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ history.log       # Step execution log\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ src/                      # Project source\nÔööÔöÇÔöÇ .git/\n```\n\n### Examples:\n\nLocated in `/workspace/examples/`:\n1. **`ruby-calculator/`** ÔÇö Complete Ruby project with tests, linters, quality checks\n2. **`mini-redis/`** ÔÇö Redis implementation in C\n3. **`gemini-browser/`** ÔÇö Browser-like project\n4. **`hello-world/`** ÔÇö Minimal workflow examples\n\n---\n\n## KEY COMMAND REFERENCE\n\n**Installation:**\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\ncd cloche\nmake install PREFIX=~/.local\nexport PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n```\n\n**Initialize Project:**\n```bash\ncloche init\n# or with custom options:\ncloche init --workflow my-workflow --base-image ubuntu:24.04\n```\n\n**Run Workflow:**\n```bash\ncloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Implement feature X\"\n```\n\n**Monitor Progress:**\n```bash\ncloche status <run-id>\ncloche logs <run-id> -f\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\n**List Runs:**\n```bash\ncloche list          # Last hour\ncloche list --all    # All runs\n```\n\n---\n\n## ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES\n\n**Daemon Configuration:**\n- `CLOCHE_LISTEN` ÔÇö Listen address (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n- `CLOCHE_DB` ÔÇö SQLite database path (default: `cloche.db`)\n- `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` ÔÇö `docker` or `local` (default: `docker`)\n- `CLOCHE_IMAGE` ÔÇö Default Docker image (default: `cloche-agent:latest`)\n- `CLOCHE_HTTP` ÔÇö HTTP address for web dashboard (unset by default)\n- `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` ÔÇö Path to cloche-agent binary (auto-detected)\n- `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` ÔÇö Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts)\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` ÔÇö Passed into Docker containers for agent steps\n- `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` ÔÇö Comma-separated extra bind mounts (`host:container`)\n- `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` ÔÇö Comma-separated extra env vars (`KEY=VALUE`)\n\n**Client Configuration:**\n- `CLOCHE_ADDR` ÔÇö Daemon gRPC address (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n- `CLOCHE_HTTP` ÔÇö Daemon HTTP address (default: `localhost:8080`)\n\n---\n\n## FILE PATHS ÔÇö ABSOLUTE\n\n**Key Documentation Files:**\n- `/workspace/README.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- `/workspace/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/workspace/AGENTS.md`\n\n**Source Code:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` ÔÇö CLI entry point and command implementations\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` ÔÇö `cloche init` implementation with templates\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/` ÔÇö Daemon source\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/` ÔÇö In-container agent source\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/` ÔÇö Workflow DSL parser and lexer\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/` ÔÇö Core types (Workflow, Step, Run)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/` ÔÇö Docker, SQLite, gRPC implementations\n\n**Configuration & Templates:**\n- `/workspace/.cloche/Dockerfile` ÔÇö Project's Dockerfile template\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` ÔÇö Project's development workflow\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` ÔÇö Project's host orchestration workflow\n- `/workspace/.cloche/config.toml` ÔÇö Project configuration\n- `/workspace/.cloche/prompts/` ÔÇö Prompt templates directory\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/` ÔÇö Host-side scripts directory\n\n**Examples:**\n- `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/` ÔÇö Complete Ruby project example\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/` ÔÇö C Redis implementation\n- `/workspace/examples/hello-world/` ÔÇö Minimal examples\n\n**Build Artifacts:**\n- `/workspace/Makefile` ÔÇö Build system\n- `/workspace/go.mod` ÔÇö Go module definition (Go 1.25.3)\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive report provides all the details needed to write a complete getting-started guide for cloche."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aec0f283d314d05c4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68588\ntool_uses: 54\nduration_ms: 86288</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"caefa047-41e4-4a64-a92e-dbea2379cd5a","uuid":"340d9fb7-fb97-475a-b412-b43286761ffd","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the cloche codebase to find all details needed for a getting-started guide. Specifically find:\n\n1. How to build/install cloche ÔÇö look at Makefile, go.mod, cmd/ directories, any install scripts\n2. The `cloche init` command ÔÇö what it does, what files it creates, what flags it accepts\n3. Dockerfile configuration ÔÇö what the default/template Dockerfile looks like in .cloche/, any special requirements\n4. Workflow DSL setup ÔÇö look at docs/workflows.md, example .cloche files, the DSL syntax\n5. Pointers to other documentation ÔÇö what's in the docs/ directory\n\nRead all relevant files fully. I need exact command names, flags, file paths, and behaviors.","agentId":"aec0f283d314d05c4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have comprehensive information about the cloche codebase. Let me compile the complete findings into a detailed report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the cloche codebase and compiled all the details needed for a comprehensive getting-started guide. Here are the complete findings:\n\n---\n\n# CLOCHE GETTING-STARTED GUIDE ÔÇö RESEARCH FINDINGS\n\n## 1. BUILD/INSTALL\n\n**Build from Source:**\n- **Makefile targets:**\n  - `make build` Ôćĺ Builds all three binaries to `bin/` directory\n  - `make docker-build` Ôćĺ Builds the cloche-agent Docker image from `.cloche/Dockerfile`\n  - `make install PREFIX=~/.local` Ôćĺ Builds all binaries, builds Docker image, installs to prefix (default: `~/.local/bin/`), and starts daemon\n  - `make test` Ôćĺ Runs all tests\n  - `make test-short` Ôćĺ Runs tests, skipping slow ones\n  - `make lint` Ôćĺ Runs `go vet`\n  - `make proto` Ôćĺ Regenerates gRPC code from protobuf\n  - `make clean` Ôćĺ Removes `bin/` directory\n\n**Installation Methods:**\n- Build from source: `git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git && cd cloche && make install`\n- Via `go install`: `go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche@latest` (requires manual Docker image build)\n- Pre-built binaries: Planned but not yet available\n- Homebrew: Planned but not yet available\n- Docker daemon: Planned future option\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- Go 1.25+ (for building)\n- Docker (for running workflows)\n- Git (for result extraction via worktrees)\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` environment variable (for agent steps)\n\n**Installation Verification:**\n```bash\ncloche --help\ncloched --help\nmake docker-build\ncloche list\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. CLOCHE INIT COMMAND\n\n**Command Syntax:**\n```bash\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n```\n\n**Flags:**\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name; creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche` |\n| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for generated Dockerfile |\n\n**Files Created:**\nThe command scaffolds a `.cloche/` directory structure with these files (skips existing files):\n\n1. **`.cloche/<workflow>.cloche`** ÔÇö Container workflow definition (named after `--workflow` flag)\n2. **`.cloche/Dockerfile`** ÔÇö Container image definition\n3. **`.cloche/config.toml`** ÔÇö Project configuration with settings like `active`, `orchestration`, `evolution`\n4. **`.cloche/host.cloche`** ÔÇö Host orchestration workflow (runs on host machine)\n5. **`.cloche/prompts/implement.md`** ÔÇö Prompt template for implementation step\n6. **`.cloche/prompts/fix.md`** ÔÇö Prompt template for fixing failures\n7. **`.cloche/prompts/update-docs.md`** ÔÇö Prompt template for documentation updates\n8. **`.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh`** ÔÇö Bash script to generate prompts from task info\n9. **`.cloche/overrides/`** ÔÇö Directory for container-specific file overrides\n10. **`.cloche/version`** ÔÇö Version marker file\n\n**Directories Created:**\n- `.cloche/` ÔÇö Main configuration directory\n- `.cloche/prompts/` ÔÇö Prompt template directory\n- `.cloche/scripts/` ÔÇö Host-side script directory\n- `.cloche/overrides/` ÔÇö Container override files directory\n\n**Gitignore Modifications:**\nAdds patterns:\n- `.cloche/*-*-*/` ÔÇö Runtime directories (run IDs with hyphens)\n- `.cloche/run-*/` ÔÇö Legacy run directories\n- `.cloche/attempt_count/` ÔÇö Retry tracking\n- `.gitworktrees/` ÔÇö Git worktrees for result extraction\n\n**Post-Init Instructions Printed:**\n```\nNext steps:\n  1. Edit .cloche/config.toml ÔÇö set active = true to auto-run on startup\n  2. Edit .cloche/<workflow>.cloche ÔÇö adjust test command for your project\n  3. Edit .cloche/Dockerfile ÔÇö add your project's dependencies\n  4. Edit .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh ÔÇö customize prompt generation\n  5. Add container-specific overrides to .cloche/overrides/ (e.g. CLAUDE.md)\n  6. docker build -t cloche-agent -f .cloche/Dockerfile .\n  7. cloche run --workflow <workflow> --prompt \"...\"\n```\n\n**Requirement:** Must be run from inside a git repository.\n\n---\n\n## 3. DOCKERFILE CONFIGURATION\n\n**Template Location:** `.cloche/Dockerfile`\n\n**Generated Template Default:**\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\n\n# Add your project's dependencies here.\n# Example:\n#   RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n#   RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Base Image:** `cloche-base:latest` (default, customizable via `--base-image` flag)\n\n**Base Image Contents:**\nThe `cloche-base:latest` image includes:\n- Debian 12-slim base\n- `git` (for version control and commits)\n- `make` (for build commands)\n- `ca-certificates` (for HTTPS)\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- Non-root `agent` user\n- Working directory at `/workspace` owned by `agent`\n\n**Dockerfile Requirements (Must Have):**\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies\n- Any coding agents your workflow requires (e.g. `claude` CLI)\n\n**Example Customization (Ruby):**\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y ruby bundler\nRUN rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Example Customization (Go):**\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\nCOPY --from=golang:1.25 /usr/local/go /usr/local/go\nENV PATH=\"/usr/local/go/bin:${PATH}\"\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Example with Claude Code:**\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y nodejs npm\nRUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\nRUN rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Important:** The generated Dockerfile is a template. Customize it for your project's specific dependencies before running workflows.\n\n---\n\n## 4. WORKFLOW DSL SETUP\n\n**Workflow Files:** `.cloche/*.cloche` (container workflows) or `.cloche/host.cloche` (host workflows)\n\n**Syntax Overview:**\n```\nworkflow \"<name>\" {\n  step <step_name> {\n    prompt = file(\"path/to/prompt.md\")     # OR\n    run = \"shell command\"                  # OR\n    workflow_name = \"other-workflow\"       # (host only)\n    results = [result1, result2, ...]\n    [optional config]\n  }\n  \n  step1:result -> step2\n  step2:result -> done\n  step1:other -> abort\n}\n```\n\n**Step Types:**\n1. **Agent step** ÔÇö has `prompt` field; invokes a coding agent\n2. **Script step** ÔÇö has `run` field; executes a shell command\n3. **Workflow step** ÔÇö has `workflow_name` field; dispatches a container workflow (host only)\n\n**Result Declaration:**\nSteps declare their possible results: `results = [success, fail]` or `results = [success, fail, give-up]`\n\n**Wiring (Graph Edges):**\n- `step:result -> next_step` ÔÇö Route based on reported result\n- `step:result -> done` ÔÇö Success terminal\n- `step:result -> abort` ÔÇö Failure terminal\n- `collect all(step1:result, step2:result) -> done` ÔÇö Synchronize parallel branches\n\n**Built-in Terminals:**\n- `done` ÔÇö Successful completion\n- `abort` ÔÇö Failure/error completion\n\n**Key Configuration Options:**\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template for agent steps |\n| `run` | string | Shell command for script steps |\n| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch (host only) |\n| `results` | ident list | Declared result names |\n| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before auto `give-up` (e.g. `\"2\"`) |\n| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration (e.g. `\"30m\"`, default: 30m) |\n| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s); comma-separated for fallback chains (e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`) |\n| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments |\n| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include validation output in prompt |\n| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as prompt |\n\n**Container Configuration Block:**\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Wire Output Mappings:**\nExtract JSON values from step output and inject as environment variables:\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\n**Example Complete Workflow:**\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> fix\n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n  fix:give-up -> abort\n}\n```\n\n**Prompt Assembly (Agent Steps):**\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from:\n1. Step template content (from `prompt` field)\n2. User request (from `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`, prefixed with `## User Request`)\n3. Validation output (if `feedback = \"true\"`, from `.cloche/output/*.log` files)\n4. Result selection instructions (with possible results listed)\n\n**Result Protocol:**\nSteps report results by printing a marker to stdout:\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<result_name>\n```\nExamples: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:fail`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`\n\nFor script steps:\n- Exit 0 = `success`\n- Exit non-zero = `fail`\n\n**Comments:**\nUse `//` for line comments:\n```\nimplement:success -> test  // This is a comment\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. DOCUMENTATION POINTERS\n\n**Documentation Files Location:** `/workspace/docs/`\n\n### Available Documentation:\n\n1. **`docs/INSTALL.md`** ÔÇö Full installation guide\n   - Build from source\n   - `go install` method\n   - Pre-built binaries (planned)\n   - Homebrew (planned)\n   - Docker-only usage (planned)\n   - Verification steps\n   - Upgrade instructions\n\n2. **`docs/USAGE.md`** ÔÇö Complete CLI and usage reference (20KB)\n   - Core concepts\n   - Workflow DSL full syntax\n   - Step configuration options\n   - The `file()` function\n   - Container and host blocks\n   - Wiring syntax and output mappings\n   - Retry loops, parallel branches, collect/join\n   - Result protocol\n   - Prompt assembly\n   - Agent command resolution\n   - Complete example with parallel validation\n   - Container isolation model\n   - **CLI Reference:**\n     - `cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]`\n     - `cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]`\n     - `cloche status <run-id>`\n     - `cloche list [--all]`\n     - `cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]`\n     - `cloche poll <run-id>`\n     - `cloche stop <run-id>`\n     - `cloche delete <container-or-run-id>`\n     - `cloche health`\n     - `cloche get <key>`\n     - `cloche set <key> <value>`\n     - `cloche tasks [--project <dir>]`\n     - `cloche shutdown`\n   - Project layout\n   - Daemon configuration (environment variables)\n   - Client configuration\n   - Dockerfile requirements\n   - Build commands\n\n3. **`docs/workflows.md`** ÔÇö Workflow DSL reference (9KB)\n   - Workflow locations (container vs. host)\n   - DSL concepts\n   - Step types\n   - Syntax examples\n   - Key properties\n   - Wire output mappings\n   - Host block configuration\n   - Host workflow example with three phases\n   - Execution model\n\n4. **`docs/plans/`** ÔÇö Architecture and design documents\n   - `2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md` ÔÇö Complete system design and architecture\n   - `2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md` ÔÇö Implementation details\n   - `2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md` ÔÇö `cloche init` command design\n   - `2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md` ÔÇö Self-evolution feature\n   - `2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md` ÔÇö Base Docker image design\n   - `2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` ÔÇö Host workflow design\n   - And many others covering specific features\n\n### Project Layout Documentation:\n```\nmy-project/\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ .cloche/\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ config.toml           # Project configuration\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompts/              # Prompt templates\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ implement.md\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ fix.md\nÔöé   Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ update-docs.md\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\nÔöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\nÔöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ prompt.txt        # User prompt\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ context.json      # Shared key-value store\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ output/\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ full.log      # Unified log\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ test.log      # Per-step script output\nÔöé       Ôöé   ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\nÔöé       ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ attempt_count/    # Retry counters\nÔöé       ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ history.log       # Step execution log\nÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ src/                      # Project source\nÔööÔöÇÔöÇ .git/\n```\n\n### Examples:\n\nLocated in `/workspace/examples/`:\n1. **`ruby-calculator/`** ÔÇö Complete Ruby project with tests, linters, quality checks\n2. **`mini-redis/`** ÔÇö Redis implementation in C\n3. **`gemini-browser/`** ÔÇö Browser-like project\n4. **`hello-world/`** ÔÇö Minimal workflow examples\n\n---\n\n## KEY COMMAND REFERENCE\n\n**Installation:**\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\ncd cloche\nmake install PREFIX=~/.local\nexport PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n```\n\n**Initialize Project:**\n```bash\ncloche init\n# or with custom options:\ncloche init --workflow my-workflow --base-image ubuntu:24.04\n```\n\n**Run Workflow:**\n```bash\ncloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Implement feature X\"\n```\n\n**Monitor Progress:**\n```bash\ncloche status <run-id>\ncloche logs <run-id> -f\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\n**List Runs:**\n```bash\ncloche list          # Last hour\ncloche list --all    # All runs\n```\n\n---\n\n## ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES\n\n**Daemon Configuration:**\n- `CLOCHE_LISTEN` ÔÇö Listen address (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n- `CLOCHE_DB` ÔÇö SQLite database path (default: `cloche.db`)\n- `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` ÔÇö `docker` or `local` (default: `docker`)\n- `CLOCHE_IMAGE` ÔÇö Default Docker image (default: `cloche-agent:latest`)\n- `CLOCHE_HTTP` ÔÇö HTTP address for web dashboard (unset by default)\n- `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` ÔÇö Path to cloche-agent binary (auto-detected)\n- `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` ÔÇö Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts)\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` ÔÇö Passed into Docker containers for agent steps\n- `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` ÔÇö Comma-separated extra bind mounts (`host:container`)\n- `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` ÔÇö Comma-separated extra env vars (`KEY=VALUE`)\n\n**Client Configuration:**\n- `CLOCHE_ADDR` ÔÇö Daemon gRPC address (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n- `CLOCHE_HTTP` ÔÇö Daemon HTTP address (default: `localhost:8080`)\n\n---\n\n## FILE PATHS ÔÇö ABSOLUTE\n\n**Key Documentation Files:**\n- `/workspace/README.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- `/workspace/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/workspace/AGENTS.md`\n\n**Source Code:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` ÔÇö CLI entry point and command implementations\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` ÔÇö `cloche init` implementation with templates\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/` ÔÇö Daemon source\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/` ÔÇö In-container agent source\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/` ÔÇö Workflow DSL parser and lexer\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/` ÔÇö Core types (Workflow, Step, Run)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/` ÔÇö Docker, SQLite, gRPC implementations\n\n**Configuration & Templates:**\n- `/workspace/.cloche/Dockerfile` ÔÇö Project's Dockerfile template\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` ÔÇö Project's development workflow\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` ÔÇö Project's host orchestration workflow\n- `/workspace/.cloche/config.toml` ÔÇö Project configuration\n- `/workspace/.cloche/prompts/` ÔÇö Prompt templates directory\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/` ÔÇö Host-side scripts directory\n\n**Examples:**\n- `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/` ÔÇö Complete Ruby project example\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/` ÔÇö C Redis implementation\n- `/workspace/examples/hello-world/` ÔÇö Minimal examples\n\n**Build Artifacts:**\n- `/workspace/Makefile` ÔÇö Build system\n- `/workspace/go.mod` ÔÇö Go module definition (Go 1.25.3)\n\n---\n